<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy & Terms">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <div class="content-box">
      <h1>Privacy Policy & Terms of Use</h1>
      
      <p class="update-date"><em>Last Updated: January 2026</em></p>

      <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
      
      <h3>Information we collect</h3>
      <p>This website is primarily educational and collects minimal personal information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact Forms:</strong> When you submit feedback or contact forms, we collect your name, email address, and message content</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We may collect anonymous usage statistics to improve our website (page views, time on site, navigation patterns)</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> This site uses minimal cookies for basic functionality. No advertising or tracking cookies are used</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How We use your information</h3>
      <p>Information collected through this website is used to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your inquiries and feedback</li>
        <li>Improve our curriculum and educational materials</li>
        <li>Communicate about programs and opportunities (only if you've requested)</li>
        <li>Analyze website usage to enhance user experience</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Data Protection</h3>
      <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>All form submissions are transmitted securely</li>
        <li>Personal information is stored securely and accessed only by authorized personnel</li>
        <li>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes</li>
        <li>We retain personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined above</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Children's Privacy</h3>
      <p>This website is designed for educational use and may be accessed by minors. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. If you believe a child has provided personal information without consent, please contact us immediately.</p>

      <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
      <p>This website may use third-party services such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Formspree:</strong> For contact form processing (see Formspree's privacy policy)</li>
        <li><strong>GitHub Pages:</strong> For website hosting (see GitHub's privacy policy)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These services have their own privacy policies, which we encourage you to review.</p>

      <h2>Terms of Use</h2>

      <h3>Educational Use</h3>
      <p>All content on this website is provided for educational purposes. You may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access and use curriculum materials for educational purposes</li>
        <li>Download resources for classroom use</li>
        <li>Share links to this website</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Content Ownership</h3>
      <p>Unless otherwise noted, all content, curriculum materials, and resources on this website are:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Developed by WIAA and Iowa State University</li>
        <li>Protected by copyright</li>
        <li>Available for non-commercial educational use</li>
      </ul>
      <p>For commercial use or redistribution, please contact us for permission.</p>

      <h3>Downloadable Resources</h3>
      <p>Downloadable materials (worksheets, presentations, activities) are provided as-is for educational use. You may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use materials in your classroom or educational setting</li>
        <li>Modify materials for your specific needs</li>
        <li>Credit WIAA when sharing or presenting these materials</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Disclaimer</h3>
      <p>While we strive for accuracy, WIAA makes no warranties about the completeness, reliability, or accuracy of this information. The curriculum and materials are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind.</p>

      <h3>External Links</h3>
      <p>This website may contain links to external sites. WIAA is not responsible for the privacy practices or content of external websites.</p>

      <h3>Changes to This Policy</h3>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy and Terms of Use periodically. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.</p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, Terms of Use, or how we handle your information, please contact us:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:wiaa@iastate.edu">wiaa@iastate.edu</a></li>
        <li><strong>Phone:</strong> (555) 123-4567</li>
        <li><strong>Mail:</strong> 716 Farm House Lane, Ames, Iowa 50011</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="cta-section">
        <a href="/WIAA/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
        <a href="/WIAA" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-left: 15px;">Return Home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

